parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction or fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden and unpredictable total brake failure
brake pedal goes to the floor with no response
loud noises from the engine compartment
ABS noise without brake action
brake warning lights illuminated
loss of brake pressure
jerky or abrupt braking behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the regenerative brake system can cause jerky or abrupt braking behavior, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Aggressive braking behavior
jerky or abrupt braking
brake pedal hesitation
brake warning lights illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or even fires, which can result in serious injury or property damage.
symptoms: The brake
ABS
warning
and traction control lights are illuminated
the vehicle accelerates without throttle input
the vehicle is difficult to brake
a weird hum is present at power-on
the vehicle displays warning lights
and the vehicle catches fire while charging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or even fires, which can result in serious injury or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while charging
the vehicle displays warning lights
the vehicle accelerates without throttle input
the vehicle is difficult to brake
and the charging unit is suspected to be the root cause of the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 12V battery can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or difficulty braking, which can result in serious injury or property damage.
symptoms: The brake
ABS
warning
and traction control lights are illuminated

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the occupant detection system can cause the airbag to be disabled even when a passenger is present, which can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag disabled light illuminates when a passenger is sitting in the seat
the airbag is not deployed despite the presence of a passenger
inconsistent airbag deployment with different passengers.
